<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-5617] T(SSL)Socket TCP keep-alive incorrectly applies SO_KEEPALIVE to IPPROTO_TCP</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-5617</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;SO_KEEPALIVE&lt;/tt&gt; is a &lt;tt&gt;SOL_SOCKET&lt;/tt&gt;-level socket option.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At least on my (Linux-based) system, this causes &lt;tt&gt;IPPROTO_TCP&lt;/tt&gt; &lt;tt&gt;TCP_DEFER_ACCEPT&lt;/tt&gt; to be set to 1 when a &lt;tt&gt;T(SSL)Socket&lt;/tt&gt; is created with &lt;tt&gt;socket_keepalive&lt;/tt&gt; set and keep-alives are not enabled.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See also: &lt;a href=&quot;https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man7/socket.7.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man7/socket.7.html&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/winsock/so-keepalive&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/winsock/so-keepalive&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
